 One direct technique is via the normalization of the Parry-Gelfond measure.
 The function in eqn 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:invariant measure"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 or more generally 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:generalized-eigenfunction"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 can be integrated in a straight-forward manner.
 One has
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
I\left(\beta;z\right)=\int_{0}^{1}\nu_{\beta;z}\left(x\right)dx=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{z^{n}}{\beta^{n}}\int_{0}^{1}d_{n}\left(x\right)dx=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{z^{n}}{\beta^{n}}T^{n}\left(\frac{\beta}{2}\right)
\]

\end_inset

